  "prompt": "How can I watch One Piece without all the filler episodes?",
  "response": "If you want to watch \"One Piece\" without the filler episodes, there are a few methods you can use to skip the filler while still enjoying the main storyline:\n\n1. **Filler Guides**: Refer to online filler guides that provide a list of which episodes are considered filler. Websites like Anime Filler List or various fan sites often have detailed lists showing which episodes are canon and which ones are fillers.\n\n2. **Streaming Services**: Check if the streaming service you are using (like Crunchyroll, Funimation, or Netflix) has an option to filter out filler episodes, although this feature is not commonly available.\n\n3. **Episode Lists**: Use an episode list that highlights the canon episodes. Many sites offer summaries and details about which episodes are essential to the main plot.\n\n4. **Watch the Movies**: Some of the \"One Piece\" movies provide retellings of major arcs without filler content. However, not all movies are aligned exactly with the storyline, so be sure to check which ones are useful for your viewing.\n\n5. **Use a Completionist Approach**: If you\u2019re committed to enjoying the series fully, you might also consider watching the fillers \u2013 some fans find enjoyment in them, and they can provide additional context and character development.\n\nAs of now, here\u2019s a breakdown of episodes considered filler (this list may change with new developments in the series):\n\n- Episodes 4-5: \"The First Challenge!\" and \"The Capture of the Witch!\" \n- Episodes 91-92: \"Buggy's Big Adventure!\" and \"The Great Captain's Battle!\"\n- Episodes 196-207: \"G8 Arc\" (Generally, this arc is also well-received).\n- Episodes 213-219: Includes filler arcs and a few non-canon episodes. \n- Episodes 783-884: Contains the \"Filler\" after the Dressrosa arc.\n\nMake sure to cross-reference with current online filler guides, as \"One Piece\" is an ongoing series, and new filler information can arise. Enjoy your viewing!",
